rComments: Great professor and really cares about his students. This class was really easy since the tests were open book and the questions could be found verbatim in the text. Evaluations were two midterms, a final, an article review assignment and lab participation. Overall, great class and a good GPA booster.

He is very passionate about what he 's teaching which makes the learning experience much higher quality. His lectures are not very detailed, instead he relies on the textbook to teach everything. His midterms and exams are fair, based on the textbook. Overall, I would recommend taking a class with him.
easy to follow but the PowerPoint is subpar.

He is a good prof, cares about his students. I loved the coglab activities we did during the lab, very interesting and you get tested on some of them. Had 2 midterms + presentation/paper + final. Have to read textbook, don't necessarily have to go to class but helpful. Overall class was good, I enjoyed, he made the content fun and interesting.

Dr. Davidson is better than these reviews say. People don't like that his slide decks are fairly short and are just an overview of the textbook chapter. You WILL have to read the textbook to do well, but if you do so, it's an easy A. 2 midterms, 1 final, 6 or 7 labs (marked for attendance, no reports) and 1 group paper + presentation.

Hes a good guy, but personally I found his lectures dry, especially as I wasnt interested in the material in the first place. I would recommend investing in a test bank... overall not a difficult course, just not super interesting.

Worst Professor ever. Doesn't respect at all the amount of money students spend on tuition. His online lectures are twice a week and are in the format of recorded audios over PowerPoint slides. His lectures do not contain any information and are only 10 minutes long. Avoid this professor at all costs and make the money you spend on tuition worth.

Im surprised there are so many negative reviews. Maybe my experience was different because the class was entirely online, but his expectations are clear and all tests are super fair. Easy to follow lectures and average amount of readings. He was a bit disorganized in the beginning with instructions for the discussions but thats my only con.

Honestly great prof. Expectations are clear, do the weekly reflections that are in the PowerPoints and study the textbook for the exams (all MC) and its an easy A+. Class topic is also interesting which makes the readings easier to get through. 100% would recommend this class with prof Davidson
I was sad to see the negative reviews. I have really enjoyed this professor. He's helpful, accessible, brilliant, and funny.

2 midterms worth 20% each, paper and short presentation worth 15% that is done with a partner, labs worth 10% and exam worth 35%. Classes do not relate to tests at all. He also is not the best at answering questions. His answers tend to be ambiguous. Just study the textbook heavily and you'll do well. Paper and labs were nice grade boosters

Spends lectures focused on one minuscule aspect of the textbook and stretching it until its loaded with too many examples and very little textbook knowledge. However, he does not read the textbook, we had a MCQ that was removed from the midterm because it was never covered. But he will throw one random thing in a lecture and put in on the midterm

He's a good prof, just a bit absent-minded and awkward at times. Lectures mostly consist of examples that build on textbook content. Not too interesting. Group presentations seem ominous, but are quite simple and graded very fairly. Go to labs to boost your grade 10%. Exams were MC/short answer, harder than expected.

Very conflicted.. He really means well in his teaching but he's not great. Seems very nice but doesn't know the material. Reads right off the slides and the exams don't even reflect lectures. Oddly specific MC questions from the textbook, short answer questions saved my grade. Unless you're prepared to memorize the book i don't recommend this prof.

he is obviously passionate about the content, however he does not convey the material in an effective way. Often gets lost in his own thoughts and this results in the class having no idea what he is talking about. Reads directly off of the powerpoints and gives no information about what will be on the exams. Do not recommend
teacherRatingTags: ['Test heavy', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Dr. Davidson is honestly a very good prof! Very surprised at the low score here. He is very engaging and obviously enthusiastic, uses tons of examples from research to illustrate the subject matter. Slides must be filled in but aren't nearly as important as the textbook. Straightforward exams. Easy paper. Very fair!!! Super fun guy too! Recommend.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Some people just should not be teachers, and he is one of those people. Awful at explaining things in class. He's obviously an intelligent person, but quite inarticulate. I don't know what the hell he is saying like 50% of the time. Furthermore chooses to cover the easy material from the text in class rather than explaining harder material. AVOID

Professor Davidson clearly enjoys what he teaches, and presents many opportunities for students to get involved in research on topics covered. His lectures are interesting, but almost irrelevant. There is no correlation between time spent on a subject and importance to the test. The biggest question from the final was from a chapter we didn't cover

Although he is clearly intelligent, he should not be a professor. Inarticulate and confusing when presenting course material, evaluations that do not reflect what was discussed during lectures, etc. Heavily reliant on textbook - majority of exams cover obscure material from within the textbook that was never even mentioned during class.

I really liked him. He made his classes interesting and has a real passion for the subject matter. Read the textbook and the notes and you will do well on the exams. Labs are a pain, but are mandatory. Overall, I would recommend
Is not knowledgeable about the material or the course details (i.e. midterm or exam tips). Reads off the PowerPoint directly and gives no midterm review at all.
He is the sweetest man. He has inspired me to undertake a career in cognitive neuropsychology and make breakfast every day (it's an executive function task!)

AVOID AT ALL COST! can't explain anything properly, when a student asks him a question he stares at the floor or ceiling and avoids answering. 2 midterms and a final, if you have him then study diagrams that are ridiculous and he'll put it in black and white!
Made things kind of interesting. Recommended.
Boring teacher. Exames were somewhat hard. Had to attend class because he did not provide full notes. I do not recommend anyone to take this teacher.

Professor Davidson provides powerpoint slides which are very helpful, however they are not fully filled out and you need to copy the info when you are in class.  He tries to make things easier by providing past copies of mid-terms and exams.  No projects, 2 mid-terms and a final which consist of m/c and short answer.
Alright teacher just not engaging n class has boring material n he didnt help trying 2 understand material!
No Comments
